<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 1:33PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...BLUSTERY WITH SCATTERED SNOW SHOWERS...
The wind is going to be gusty through this afternoon. Most will
experience gusts in the 20 to 30 mph range, but a few gusts over
40 mph will occur along some of the ridges and nearby valleys.
At the same time, snow showers will be scattered to numerous,
moreso over the West Virginia mountains into the higher terrain of
southwest Virginia into the North Carolina High Country. Most will
see a dusting or less while the higher elevations could get an
inch or so through dusk.
Those traveling or outdoors should use caution due to the winds.
Higher profile vehicles like tractor-trailers will be impacted
most. Those driving over the mountains should be alert to slick
roads.
Winds and snow showers will diminish by late evening for much of
the area.</description>
